content:
@mcneazy for pristine pop, edit the fuck outta them drums, get them gridded and feeling great. 9 times outta ten gridding them will actually improve the feel, and in the spots where it doesn’t you can always comp back in. 
Then edit bass to the kick & snare, when it’s right the bottom will tell you. 
Then call Beckley to edit your vocals.

Thanks @philbarnes !

@Slow Hand I think just good sounds that I don't need to play with very much to get a vibe. 
Think co-write sessions with artists in the room, smash the drum pattern out in 10 minutes and then continue to work on the song without having to enter "Engineer" mode playing with plugins to make the drum sound passable.
